The paper focuses on deep neural networks for image compression, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a context model, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a new technique for navigating the trade-off between reconstruction error and entropy, which involves optimizing the model's parameters (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses a convolutional auto-encoder, which is a type of neural network commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
